Source: ouaexp
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Maintainer: @MAINTAINER@
Homepage: https://github.com/sanny32/OpenUaExplorer
Standards-Version: 4.6.2

Package: ouaexp
Architecture: @ARCH@
# Qt loads OpenSSL with dlopen, so dpkg-shlibdeps cannot see the dependency.
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libssl3 | libssl3t64
Description: OPC UA client for exploring and monitoring OPC UA servers
 OpenUaExplorer is an open source OPC UA client for browsing, inspecting,
 and monitoring OPC UA servers.
 .
  * Browse the OPC UA address space and inspect node attributes.
  * View Data Access, subscriptions, events, and history panels.
  * Plot live and historical values on charts.
  * Connect anonymously, with a username, or with a client certificate.
 .
 The package is self-contained: it carries the Qt libraries it was built
 against, together with the Qt OpcUa module and its open62541 backend, in a
 private directory under /usr/lib/ouaexp. Only the C, C++, OpenGL and xcb
 runtimes come from the distribution, so the package installs on any
 Debian-compatible system that is at least as new as the one it was built on.
